    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Mavroyeni Bey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of your
                    note of the 22d instant, in relation to the interview which you had with the
                    late Secretary of State on April 4 last.</p>
                <p>In the light of your statements it may be that Mr. Gresham referred to the
                    ultimate firman fortifying and making perpetual the concession of the irade
                    issued in January to the girls’ school at Scutari. The firman is still
                    awaited.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
